definition.value: A heart disease that is characterized by any structural or functional cardiacdisorder that impairs the ability of the heart to fill with or pump a sufficient amount ofblood throughout the body.
A disease that has_material_basis_in genetic variations in the human genome.

A congestive heart failure that involves a failure of the right side of the heart and is characterized by an enlargement of the right ventricle of the heart as a response to increased resistance or high blood pressure in the lungs.
A dementia that involves impairments in cognitive function caused by problems in blood vessels that feed the brain.
